WEBVTT

1
00:00:07.308 --> 00:00:08.809
"Progress" is a bad word
around here.

2
00:00:09.677 --> 00:00:12.146
- Clear the road!
- There's a standoff between rez

3
00:00:12.213 --> 00:00:13.681
and truckers trying to get
to that new mine.

4
00:00:13.814 --> 00:00:15.449
All y'all. out of here!

5
00:00:15.549 --> 00:00:16.784
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

6
00:00:16.884 --> 00:00:18.519
so you got to hide behind
a federal badge.

7
00:00:20.821 --> 00:00:22.190
These bullets are meant for us.

8
00:00:22.290 --> 00:00:23.957
Shooters are the Clegg brothers.
Carson and Wes.

9
00:00:25.426 --> 00:00:26.594
Move and you're dead!

10
00:00:26.694 --> 00:00:28.196
Life's become
more dangerous for me

11
00:00:28.296 --> 00:00:29.863
since becoming your brother.

12
00:00:29.963 --> 00:00:33.101
I guess being close
to me comes at a cost.

13
00:01:06.867 --> 00:01:08.269
Brought you gifts.

14
00:01:08.402 --> 00:01:10.938
Did you take them
from a fugitive again?

15
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:14.108
Okay. we got
battery-operated cameras.

16
00:01:14.242 --> 00:01:16.977
motion activated
and night-vision enabled.

17
00:01:17.077 --> 00:01:18.746
I'm my own security system.

18
00:01:18.879 --> 00:01:21.615
And that crack system allowed
somebody to walk up undetected.

19
00:01:21.715 --> 00:01:23.283
drop a shell casing
on your porch.

20
00:01:23.384 --> 00:01:25.719
Hell. I been through worse
than a bullet on my doormat.

21
00:01:25.786 --> 00:01:28.689
Yeah. see. I've come to learn
Montanans don't do theatrics.

22
00:01:28.756 --> 00:01:30.191
You can't ignore this threat.

23
00:01:30.258 --> 00:01:31.692
Well. I sent Tate
to his grandpa's.

24
00:01:31.759 --> 00:01:34.428
and it took you three days
to find this stuff.

25
00:01:34.527 --> 00:01:36.530
It took me a minute
to special-order the right gear

26
00:01:36.597 --> 00:01:38.166
for vengeful Cleggs.

27
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:41.101
Well. we upset a lot of people
at the standoff.

28
00:01:41.202 --> 00:01:42.603
Could be anybody.

29
00:01:42.703 --> 00:01:44.972
Randall Clegg accosted you
before you killed his son.

30
00:01:45.104 --> 00:01:48.209
I mean. you-you can bet the
field. but my money's on them.

31
00:01:49.477 --> 00:01:51.479
Well. if my past has
proved anything. whoever it is.

32
00:01:51.612 --> 00:01:55.015
they'll come for me.
some way. somehow.

33
00:01:56.283 --> 00:01:58.586
Well. let's be ready.

34
00:02:38.259 --> 00:02:41.595
Whoo! City slicker embarrassed
you at your own sport.

35
00:02:41.695 --> 00:02:44.832
Beginner's luck.

36
00:02:44.965 --> 00:02:47.968
And in my sport.
we don't use a rope.

37
00:02:48.035 --> 00:02:50.538
- I'm a bulldogger.
- A what now?

38
00:02:50.671 --> 00:02:53.874
I jump off a horse and wrestle
a 400-pound steer.

39
00:02:54.642 --> 00:02:56.410
You make a living
suplexing cows?

40
00:02:56.510 --> 00:02:58.178
It's a fair fight.

41
00:02:58.312 --> 00:02:59.880
He comes out of the chute
when I do.

42
00:02:59.980 --> 00:03:01.915
and then another cowboy
called a hazer keeps him

43
00:03:02.015 --> 00:03:03.617
on a path so I can get my angle.

44
00:03:03.684 --> 00:03:05.286
So it sounds like
the hazer does all the work.

45
00:03:05.386 --> 00:03:07.455
and then you get the glory.

46
00:03:07.521 --> 00:03:08.922
I get it.

47
00:03:09.022 --> 00:03:12.393
I feel more like a hazer
than a bulldogger as of late.

48
00:03:12.526 --> 00:03:15.128
Get the fuzzy end
of the lollipop at work?

49
00:03:16.196 --> 00:03:17.798
For now.

50
00:03:17.865 --> 00:03:20.668
But I keep delivering.
making my bosses happy.

51
00:03:20.768 --> 00:03:24.204
they'll send me back
to civilization soon enough.

52
00:03:24.305 --> 00:03:26.607
Okay. Beginner's luck. huh?

53
00:03:47.361 --> 00:03:49.162
What will it be. Henry?

54
00:03:49.228 --> 00:03:51.565
Nose paint. neat. Mads.

55
00:03:55.636 --> 00:03:57.004
You from around here?

56
00:03:57.771 --> 00:03:59.906
You're barking up
the wrong tree. hoss.

57
00:04:00.007 --> 00:04:02.576
No. Sorry. I was just wondering

58
00:04:02.676 --> 00:04:06.380
if you might know
the Clegg family?

59
00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:08.649
Nothing but trouble.

60
00:04:08.749 --> 00:04:09.617
Really?

61
00:04:09.750 --> 00:04:12.085
How much. exactly?

62
00:04:12.185 --> 00:04:14.254
'Cause I might've kicked
a hornet's nest there.

63
00:04:14.355 --> 00:04:18.826
Don't have much use
for rules the rest of us follow.

64
00:04:19.726 --> 00:04:21.661
They making threats?

65
00:04:21.762 --> 00:04:23.364
You know.

66
00:04:25.499 --> 00:04:28.268
Well. you can count on them
to deliver.

67
00:04:37.811 --> 00:04:39.513
What's with the face?

68
00:04:40.948 --> 00:04:42.550
No way Henry was
giving you a hard time.

69
00:04:42.616 --> 00:04:44.485
even though
you probably deserve one.

70
00:04:44.585 --> 00:04:47.821
No. I was just
trying to figure out

71
00:04:47.955 --> 00:04:50.157
how much I got to watch
one of my guy's backs.

72
00:04:52.025 --> 00:04:54.628
You have that math down cold.

73
00:04:54.728 --> 00:04:57.398
Team comes first.
above everything else.

74
00:04:57.465 --> 00:04:59.567
Always has. right?

75
00:05:08.809 --> 00:05:10.310
Miles?

76
00:05:10.411 --> 00:05:12.312
Sabrina. Wow.

77
00:05:12.413 --> 00:05:13.714
Been a while.

78
00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:16.584
You mean since you ghosted me
at our reunion?

79
00:05:16.684 --> 00:05:19.086
Turning your back on the rez
is kind of your thing.

80
00:05:21.188 --> 00:05:22.756
I'm messing with you. dude.

81
00:05:22.823 --> 00:05:25.526
Like I'd dunk on your ambitions
beyond Broken Rock.

82
00:05:25.659 --> 00:05:28.261
College football. Marines. MMA.

83
00:05:28.362 --> 00:05:30.163
I was always cheering you on
from afar.

84
00:05:30.297 --> 00:05:32.600
Ambitions and achievements
are two different things.

85
00:05:32.700 --> 00:05:33.933
So how are you?

86
00:05:34.001 --> 00:05:37.137
Worried there are two of us
at a cowboy bar.

87
00:05:37.204 --> 00:05:38.772
I'm on a date.

88
00:05:38.839 --> 00:05:40.273
What's your excuse?

89
00:05:40.374 --> 00:05:42.576
- Here with my teammates.
- Right.

90
00:05:42.676 --> 00:05:44.144
Heard you're a marshal now.

91
00:05:44.211 --> 00:05:45.913
How's it going?

92
00:05:46.013 --> 00:05:47.848
Traded badges to finally police
for my people.

93
00:05:47.948 --> 00:05:50.117
but some of the elders think

94
00:05:50.183 --> 00:05:52.553
being a marshal
makes me a traitor.

95
00:05:52.653 --> 00:05:54.488
Never were one for fitting in.

96
00:05:54.555 --> 00:05:55.989
But I'm still cheering.

97
00:05:58.792 --> 00:06:01.361
Don't be a stranger. Miles.

98
00:06:10.571 --> 00:06:12.840
How in the hell do we have mayo

99
00:06:12.906 --> 00:06:16.610
that's expired before
this team's even stood up?

100
00:06:16.710 --> 00:06:18.211
Sorry.

101
00:06:18.311 --> 00:06:19.547
I-I swear I'm great at this.

102
00:06:19.647 --> 00:06:21.181
She needs your bulldogger
for inspiration.

103
00:06:21.248 --> 00:06:22.950
Bulldogger?

104
00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:24.485
From "Get me out of Montana"

105
00:06:24.585 --> 00:06:27.154
to rodeo bunny
in the blink of an eye.

106
00:06:27.254 --> 00:06:29.657
You missed the action. Belle.

107
00:06:29.757 --> 00:06:30.924
Yeah. I know.

108
00:06:31.058 --> 00:06:32.493
Movie night
with my kid took priority.

109
00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:34.795
Hey.

110
00:06:34.895 --> 00:06:36.564
How are those cameras
working out?

111
00:06:36.664 --> 00:06:38.265
You ready
to bring your boy home?

112
00:06:38.365 --> 00:06:39.533
I'm gonna give it
a little more time.

113
00:06:39.633 --> 00:06:40.901
So you'd rather hang out

114
00:06:41.001 --> 00:06:42.436
where you were threatened
than with us?

115
00:06:42.536 --> 00:06:44.472
Just trying to keep you
out of the line of fire.

116
00:06:44.572 --> 00:06:46.507
Says the guy
who's gotten us shot at

117
00:06:46.607 --> 00:06:48.408
ever since he showed up.

118
00:06:48.509 --> 00:06:49.743
Harry.

119
00:06:49.877 --> 00:06:51.745
Did we know
that you were coming?

120
00:06:51.879 --> 00:06:54.381
Well. some news is
best delivered in person.

121
00:06:54.448 --> 00:06:56.584
DOJ got a complaint
from Randall Clegg.

122
00:06:56.717 --> 00:06:58.486
Claims you violated
his son's civil rights

123
00:06:58.586 --> 00:07:00.120
when you killed him.

124
00:07:00.253 --> 00:07:01.889
I violated a lot of things.
His rights wasn't one of them.

125
00:07:01.955 --> 00:07:04.992
Well. Clegg claims
that Carson dropped his weapon

126
00:07:05.092 --> 00:07:06.694
before you fired.
so Dutton's in a time-out.

127
00:07:06.760 --> 00:07:09.196
And the rest of you.
get ahead of whatever

128
00:07:09.262 --> 00:07:10.898
the DOJ investigation will find.

129
00:07:10.998 --> 00:07:13.266
Putting our teammate under the
microscope is a waste of time.

130
00:07:13.400 --> 00:07:14.868
Going shields up

131
00:07:14.935 --> 00:07:18.138
for your friend is as admirable
as it is unhelpful.

132
00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:21.274
I need an impartial review.
Deputy Cruz. you're in charge.

133
00:07:25.613 --> 00:07:27.748
Fine. I'll get things started.

134
00:07:27.815 --> 00:07:31.552
Perhaps Carson Clegg dropped
his weapon and you missed it.

135
00:07:31.619 --> 00:07:36.223
I mean. the woods are shadows.
foliage. chaos.

136
00:07:36.323 --> 00:07:37.625
I'm calmest in the chaos.

137
00:07:37.758 --> 00:07:39.392
If he dropped it.
I'd have seen it.

138
00:07:40.628 --> 00:07:41.962
You got any proof?

139
00:07:42.062 --> 00:07:44.231
I got my word.

140
00:07:47.935 --> 00:07:49.803
Good luck
with your investigation.

141
00:07:58.979 --> 00:08:02.149
Hey. you know
those claims don't have legs.

142
00:08:02.249 --> 00:08:04.251
Don't need any
with Gifford propping them up.

143
00:08:04.351 --> 00:08:05.986
I'm not waiting around
to learn my fate.

144
00:08:06.086 --> 00:08:08.155
No. you're not. You're actually
rolling out with me.

145
00:08:08.255 --> 00:08:09.757
'cause the Forest Service
needs bodies to help

146
00:08:09.857 --> 00:08:11.992
with a search and rescue
up at Bridger Range.

147
00:08:12.125 --> 00:08:13.827
and I'm betting
you know the area.

148
00:08:13.961 --> 00:08:16.463
Yeah. it's a brutal group
of steep peaks.

149
00:08:16.564 --> 00:08:19.933
Well. you up
for some man versus nature?

150
00:08:20.801 --> 00:08:22.903
Safer than what I'm facing here.

151
00:08:29.209 --> 00:08:31.144
Helicopter carrying Tom Weaver

152
00:08:31.244 --> 00:08:33.647
and his pilot called in an
SOS after the wind kicked up.

153
00:08:33.746 --> 00:08:35.816
We're still trying to locate it.

154
00:08:35.915 --> 00:08:37.484
You don't have eyes from above?

155
00:08:37.585 --> 00:08:40.352
The wind up there is a no go
for air assets. even unmanned.

156
00:08:40.453 --> 00:08:41.989
Leaves us with over
a thousand square miles

157
00:08:42.088 --> 00:08:43.724
to cover on foot and a shortage

158
00:08:43.857 --> 00:08:45.492
of search-and-rescue-qualified
Rangers.

159
00:08:45.593 --> 00:08:48.796
You two will be
handling section D4.

160
00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:50.130
Sorry to interrupt.

161
00:08:50.197 --> 00:08:52.800
Are there any updates
on my father?

162
00:08:55.368 --> 00:08:58.238
Elevation's over 8.500 feet
up there.

163
00:08:58.338 --> 00:08:59.807
Get ready for some climbing.

164
00:08:59.873 --> 00:09:01.541
Please.
I'm a damn mountain goat.

165
00:09:01.675 --> 00:09:04.377
Just try and keep up. bro.

166
00:09:05.212 --> 00:09:07.414
Be nice to get Dolly Weaver
some answers about her dad.

167
00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:10.183
Weather's only gonna get worse.
so shove off.

168
00:09:10.250 --> 00:09:11.719
We're armed. but thank you.

169
00:09:11.852 --> 00:09:15.322
Your standard issue can't handle
what's on that mountain.

170
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:25.532
Is this what

171
00:09:25.599 --> 00:09:28.235
you being hard at work
on the investigation looks like?

172
00:09:28.335 --> 00:09:29.770
Good food's in the good kitchen.

173
00:09:29.870 --> 00:09:32.305
and we've worked up
quite an appetite already.

174
00:09:33.373 --> 00:09:35.676
Okay. so. Miles said
he didn't see anything

175
00:09:35.776 --> 00:09:37.577
because he was engaged
with Wes Clegg.

176
00:09:37.678 --> 00:09:40.714
and there are no red flags
in Kayce's incident report.

177
00:09:40.781 --> 00:09:43.684
Well. you trust a Dutton's word
at your own peril.

178
00:09:43.784 --> 00:09:46.353
Okay. It's not like
Kayce is some dirty beat cop.

179
00:09:46.419 --> 00:09:48.021
So why have you decided
he's guilty?

180
00:09:48.121 --> 00:09:49.422
It's not about guilt.

181
00:09:49.522 --> 00:09:51.290
If he's here
with his own personal agenda.

182
00:09:51.391 --> 00:09:53.093
how effective can this team be?

183
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:55.729
And Dutton dragging
this team down is gonna be

184
00:09:55.829 --> 00:09:58.598
that much harder for you
to get reassigned to D.C.

185
00:09:58.699 --> 00:10:00.200
It's in your best interest

186
00:10:00.267 --> 00:10:02.435
to be very thorough
in this investigation.

187
00:10:02.535 --> 00:10:03.871
Are you telling me

188
00:10:03.971 --> 00:10:05.939
to manufacture evidence
to support Clegg's claim?

189
00:10:06.039 --> 00:10:09.943
I'm saying that even if there's
no smoke behind this Clegg fire.

190
00:10:10.077 --> 00:10:12.579
DOJ investigation's gonna find
other Dutton skeletons

191
00:10:12.680 --> 00:10:13.981
that can hurt this team.

192
00:10:14.081 --> 00:10:15.749
Best we find them ourselves.

193
00:10:15.849 --> 00:10:18.952
or get buried
when someone else does.

194
00:10:19.052 --> 00:10:20.654
You want to get out
of this ditch

195
00:10:20.788 --> 00:10:23.957
that your old team
threw you in? Hmm?

196
00:10:24.725 --> 00:10:27.661
You better get your hands dirty.

197
00:10:32.332 --> 00:10:36.069
Didn't become a marshal
to snoop on my teammates.

198
00:10:36.169 --> 00:10:38.205
Feels especially wrong
digging into a guy

199
00:10:38.305 --> 00:10:40.708
who keeps pulling our asses
out of the fire.

200
00:10:40.808 --> 00:10:42.342
This investigation's a great way

201
00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:46.313
for Gifford to destroy any trust
that we've built with Kayce.

202
00:10:46.446 --> 00:10:49.282
Clegg's fronting for sure. but
Gifford's right about one thing.

203
00:10:49.382 --> 00:10:51.484
The complaint will impact
the rest of the team.

204
00:10:51.618 --> 00:10:54.287
So. I called a friend at DOJ
from law school...

205
00:10:54.387 --> 00:10:55.823
You're a lawyer?

206
00:10:55.923 --> 00:10:57.891
That's even less believable
than you having a friend.

207
00:10:57.991 --> 00:11:00.293
Okay. I said
I went to law school.

208
00:11:00.393 --> 00:11:01.929
I didn't say I finished.

209
00:11:02.029 --> 00:11:05.132
My friend said Clegg had a local
attorney file the complaint.

210
00:11:05.232 --> 00:11:07.367
Um. an Andrew Schroeder.

211
00:11:08.501 --> 00:11:10.537
Guy has a track record of filing

212
00:11:10.637 --> 00:11:12.539
civil suits
against law enforcement.

213
00:11:12.639 --> 00:11:15.709
Huh.
Well. DOJ finding against Kayce

214
00:11:15.809 --> 00:11:17.210
would set up Clegg to sue him.

215
00:11:17.344 --> 00:11:21.048
Unless we can prove
that Carson Clegg was armed

216
00:11:21.148 --> 00:11:22.983
when he was killed.

217
00:11:24.051 --> 00:11:26.653
Sheriff's office
finish processing the site?

218
00:11:26.720 --> 00:11:29.556
Bullets fired from the Cleggs'
positions came from two weapons.

219
00:11:29.689 --> 00:11:31.992
So both men were armed.
Case closed.

220
00:11:32.092 --> 00:11:35.328
One gun was recovered from Wes.
Haven't found Carson's.

221
00:11:35.428 --> 00:11:37.330
The man fell down a damn ravine.

222
00:11:37.397 --> 00:11:38.866
The gun's probably
floating downriver.

223
00:11:38.966 --> 00:11:41.368
They know that property
better than anyone.

224
00:11:41.468 --> 00:11:45.005
Maybe they got to it
before law enforcement could.

225
00:11:45.105 --> 00:11:48.375
No gun makes clearing Kayce
even more complicated.

226
00:11:51.244 --> 00:11:53.713
I know Schroeder.

227
00:11:53.814 --> 00:11:58.218
Let me go remind him that
his new client is an outlaw.

228
00:11:58.318 --> 00:11:59.519
We should also sniff out

229
00:11:59.619 --> 00:12:02.322
if he's got any evidence
he's holding back.

230
00:12:02.422 --> 00:12:03.924
We?

231
00:12:12.699 --> 00:12:14.301
So. is the. uh. quiet man act

232
00:12:14.401 --> 00:12:15.836
'cause you're taking in
the scenery.

233
00:12:15.903 --> 00:12:18.571
or you plotting your revenge
against Clegg?

234
00:12:18.671 --> 00:12:21.741
I'm just glad he's coming
after my badge and not my kid.

235
00:12:21.842 --> 00:12:24.244
Well. Gifford's way out of line
backing up a bogus claim. man.

236
00:12:24.377 --> 00:12:28.048
He's just taking out
some old beef with my dad on me.

237
00:12:28.115 --> 00:12:29.616
So's Clegg.

238
00:12:29.716 --> 00:12:31.218
Not the first time
I've been punished

239
00:12:31.284 --> 00:12:33.420
for doing
what I thought was right.

240
00:12:33.520 --> 00:12:35.388
When was that?

241
00:12:36.289 --> 00:12:38.191
Pretty much since birth.

242
00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:42.095
- You smell that?
- Mm-hmm.

243
00:12:42.229 --> 00:12:43.530
Aviation fuel.

244
00:12:43.596 --> 00:12:46.433
Nothing brings me back
to Afghanistan faster.

245
00:12:46.533 --> 00:12:47.767
Come on.

246
00:12:59.546 --> 00:13:01.081
Whoa.

247
00:13:09.356 --> 00:13:13.260
I'm not sure Tom Weaver deserves
us risking our lives for him.

248
00:13:13.326 --> 00:13:15.728
Oh. I didn't realize
that you knew him.

249
00:13:15.795 --> 00:13:17.965
Of him. He's a transplant.

250
00:13:18.098 --> 00:13:19.399
Bought a big chunk of land

251
00:13:19.466 --> 00:13:21.468
and thinks that makes him
king of the valley.

252
00:13:21.568 --> 00:13:22.970
Oh. I see. You don't like him

253
00:13:23.103 --> 00:13:25.305
'cause he's doing a bad
impression of your dad. huh?

254
00:13:25.405 --> 00:13:27.274
Or a good one. Flying around

255
00:13:27.374 --> 00:13:29.342
in these conditions.
knowing a storm's coming in?

256
00:13:29.476 --> 00:13:31.311
These ranchers get obsessed
with their brands.

257
00:13:31.444 --> 00:13:33.813
start treating their people
like livestock.

258
00:13:35.215 --> 00:13:36.984
There's a sheen on the water.

259
00:13:40.553 --> 00:13:42.355
- Bird went down upstream.
- Mm-hmm.

260
00:13:55.635 --> 00:13:58.038
So how do you know
this fancy lawyer?

261
00:13:58.171 --> 00:13:59.772
Your husband his dentist?

262
00:13:59.839 --> 00:14:01.508
His wife queen of the PTA?

263
00:14:01.608 --> 00:14:03.343
You do couple's Pilates
together?

264
00:14:03.443 --> 00:14:06.646
Don't embarrass me
in front of him.

265
00:14:06.713 --> 00:14:08.781
Oh. why? Because he'd spread
the word at the country club?

266
00:14:11.551 --> 00:14:13.220
Look at that shine. Terry.

267
00:14:13.353 --> 00:14:15.622
It's like a Yogo sapphire.

268
00:14:15.688 --> 00:14:19.459
Well. you do love
reflective surfaces.

269
00:14:20.360 --> 00:14:21.528
Andrew.

270
00:14:21.628 --> 00:14:23.163
Belle.

271
00:14:23.230 --> 00:14:26.499
I haven't seen you since your
birdie on 18 cleaned me out.

272
00:14:26.566 --> 00:14:27.867
Damn straight.

273
00:14:28.001 --> 00:14:31.004
You here. uh.
looking for a gift for Jared?

274
00:14:31.071 --> 00:14:32.906
I'm looking out for you.

275
00:14:33.673 --> 00:14:36.376
This is my colleague.
Andrea Cruz.

276
00:14:37.177 --> 00:14:39.980
Andrew. we hear you filed
a civil rights complaint

277
00:14:40.080 --> 00:14:41.581
against our teammate.

278
00:14:42.415 --> 00:14:44.751
You've heard of privilege.

279
00:14:44.851 --> 00:14:46.886
I can't talk about my clients.

280
00:14:47.687 --> 00:14:51.058
Well. given our relationship.

281
00:14:51.158 --> 00:14:54.594
I wanted to share that the
Cleggs are facing investigations

282
00:14:54.694 --> 00:14:56.930
on the local.
state and federal level.

283
00:14:57.064 --> 00:14:58.431
How would the club feel

284
00:14:58.565 --> 00:15:01.801
about you being associated
with such lowlifes?

285
00:15:02.669 --> 00:15:04.771
Andrew. business can't be so bad

286
00:15:04.871 --> 00:15:07.941
that you have to advocate
for actual...

287
00:15:08.041 --> 00:15:09.376
criminals.

288
00:15:09.476 --> 00:15:11.244
Marshals should be
more concerned about

289
00:15:11.344 --> 00:15:13.380
the actual criminal
carrying their badge.

290
00:15:15.348 --> 00:15:17.384
Kayce is a chip off
the John Dutton block.

291
00:15:17.450 --> 00:15:21.388
thinking he can play
outside the lines.

292
00:15:22.189 --> 00:15:24.291
This'll do double duty:

293
00:15:24.424 --> 00:15:28.828
Carson's funeral
and talking to the press.

294
00:15:30.597 --> 00:15:33.400
Making noise to the media
will influence the DOJ's review

295
00:15:33.500 --> 00:15:35.068
of the complaint against Kayce.

296
00:15:35.168 --> 00:15:39.806
Everyone in Montana will cheer
when a Dutton finally learns

297
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:43.110
a badge isn't a shield
for their sins.

298
00:15:43.210 --> 00:15:46.246
Okay. so you can prove
that Carson was unarmed

299
00:15:46.346 --> 00:15:47.914
when Kayce killed him?

300
00:15:47.981 --> 00:15:49.682
Can you prove he wasn't?

301
00:15:59.959 --> 00:16:02.295
Schroeder is gonna focus
on Kayce's character

302
00:16:02.395 --> 00:16:05.132
and make him out to look like
a cowboy who ignores the rules.

303
00:16:05.265 --> 00:16:07.200
Then we need to look
into his Navy service.

304
00:16:07.300 --> 00:16:08.635
his life in Montana.

305
00:16:08.735 --> 00:16:11.271
find out
who our teammate really is.

306
00:16:11.371 --> 00:16:13.573
-Well. seems like a good time

307
00:16:13.640 --> 00:16:17.877
to remind you that killing Clegg
was justified.

308
00:16:17.977 --> 00:16:21.014
"Justified" and "right"
aren't always the same thing.

309
00:16:21.114 --> 00:16:24.917
So. what? You're... you're
a bad man for doing your job?

310
00:16:25.018 --> 00:16:28.621
There's only one person ever
believed me to be a good man.

311
00:16:28.721 --> 00:16:31.024
She's gone.

312
00:16:31.158 --> 00:16:33.860
Your teammates believe
in you. Coyo.

313
00:16:33.993 --> 00:16:35.628
Well. they're investigating me.

314
00:16:35.728 --> 00:16:38.665
I know they have to.
but when the people

315
00:16:38.765 --> 00:16:40.633
you expect to have your back
are trying to punish you.

316
00:16:40.733 --> 00:16:42.869
- well. it tells you something.
- So. what?

317
00:16:43.002 --> 00:16:45.305
You're fine
losing the badge. then?

318
00:16:46.573 --> 00:16:48.108
Whatever happens happens.

319
00:16:48.175 --> 00:16:49.676
It's kind of hard
for your teammates

320
00:16:49.776 --> 00:16:51.010
to get close to you. man.

321
00:16:51.111 --> 00:16:53.146
if you always keep them
at arm's length.

322
00:16:53.213 --> 00:16:55.014
Just 'cause I won't go
to the bar with them

323
00:16:55.115 --> 00:16:57.550
doesn't mean I wouldn't jump
into the fire for them.

324
00:16:59.052 --> 00:17:00.287
Hey.

325
00:17:01.121 --> 00:17:02.455
Eyes on the crash site.

326
00:17:02.522 --> 00:17:05.125
Mm-hmm. That's it. Let's go.

327
00:17:15.768 --> 00:17:17.704
That's far enough.

328
00:17:21.708 --> 00:17:23.276
Dismount and eat dirt.

329
00:17:25.412 --> 00:17:27.680
I just need
whatever supplies you have.

330
00:17:34.121 --> 00:17:35.388
Hey. you haven't. uh.

331
00:17:35.522 --> 00:17:38.225
seen a crashed helo
around here. have you?

332
00:17:39.025 --> 00:17:42.095
That badge.
The hell are Feds doing up here?

333
00:17:42.195 --> 00:17:44.264
It's got nothing
to do with you. okay?

334
00:17:44.364 --> 00:17:45.832
You should really put
that gun down

335
00:17:45.932 --> 00:17:48.568
before you get yourself
into some real trouble.

336
00:17:49.636 --> 00:17:51.138
Hey. look at me.

337
00:17:51.238 --> 00:17:53.406
No. no. no.
come here. look at me.

338
00:17:53.506 --> 00:17:57.377
Hey. you shoot one of us. man.
the other one's gonna kill you.

339
00:17:57.477 --> 00:17:59.112
You got it?

340
00:18:07.420 --> 00:18:09.889
Picked the wrong wagon train
to ambush.

341
00:18:11.924 --> 00:18:14.927
All right. All right.

342
00:18:15.061 --> 00:18:17.397
Wasn't gonna hurt anyone.

343
00:18:18.064 --> 00:18:19.532
Okay?

344
00:18:19.632 --> 00:18:22.802
What are you doing
living all the way up here. huh?

345
00:18:23.636 --> 00:18:25.772
Got laid off.

346
00:18:25.905 --> 00:18:28.107
Wife left. lost my house.

347
00:18:28.208 --> 00:18:30.410
I live off the land.
or I don't live at all.

348
00:18:31.578 --> 00:18:34.013
Hmm. What you want
to do with him?

349
00:18:34.113 --> 00:18:36.616
We can zip-tie him to a tree

350
00:18:36.749 --> 00:18:39.051
and just pick him up
on the way down?

351
00:18:39.118 --> 00:18:40.587
Oh.

352
00:18:40.653 --> 00:18:44.191
Be a death sentence if the storm
gets him before we do.

353
00:18:45.258 --> 00:18:46.293
Yeah.

354
00:18:46.426 --> 00:18:47.960
All right. look.

355
00:18:48.094 --> 00:18:50.096
You're gonna head down
to the ranger station.

356
00:18:50.197 --> 00:18:52.131
and you're gonna
turn yourself in.

357
00:18:54.601 --> 00:18:56.469
Yes. sir.

358
00:19:00.307 --> 00:19:01.841
Go!

359
00:19:05.278 --> 00:19:06.779
You think he'll surrender?

360
00:19:06.846 --> 00:19:09.382
I wouldn't.

361
00:19:13.019 --> 00:19:14.987
Come on.

362
00:19:16.423 --> 00:19:18.758
It feels wrong
letting that guy go.

363
00:19:18.858 --> 00:19:20.660
He lives
by the laws of nature now.

364
00:19:20.760 --> 00:19:21.994
Survive or die.

365
00:19:22.128 --> 00:19:24.597
Kind of envy
the lack of gray area out here.

366
00:19:24.697 --> 00:19:26.333
Mm.

367
00:19:27.500 --> 00:19:30.370
False summit. Son of a bitch.

368
00:19:30.503 --> 00:19:32.605
Going around takes time
we don't have.

369
00:19:32.705 --> 00:19:34.841
Only option's straight up.

370
00:19:34.974 --> 00:19:37.877
Well. vertical climb means
travel light. travel fast.

371
00:19:38.010 --> 00:19:39.312
so essential gear only.

372
00:19:41.047 --> 00:19:42.582
Come on.

373
00:19:51.391 --> 00:19:52.992
All Kayce's deployments.

374
00:19:53.059 --> 00:19:56.128
No court-martials.
no captain's masts.

375
00:19:56.195 --> 00:19:58.465
He's basically a model sailor.

376
00:19:58.565 --> 00:20:00.633
With a Silver Star to prove it.

377
00:20:00.733 --> 00:20:04.203
Good luck to Clegg trying to
paint a war hero in a bad light.

378
00:20:04.304 --> 00:20:05.972
Well. Cal's mentioned

379
00:20:06.038 --> 00:20:09.208
that he and other
special operators struggled

380
00:20:09.309 --> 00:20:11.511
to turn off the switch
when they got out.

381
00:20:11.578 --> 00:20:13.546
"Cal's mentioned." huh?

382
00:20:13.646 --> 00:20:15.848
Rather intimate
personal history.

383
00:20:15.948 --> 00:20:20.186
Yes. sweet Andrea.
I am befriending my coworkers

384
00:20:20.253 --> 00:20:21.854
'cause I don't have
one foot out the door.

385
00:20:21.954 --> 00:20:23.790
The point is. SEALs...

386
00:20:23.890 --> 00:20:25.558
they don't have
the best reputation.

387
00:20:25.658 --> 00:20:29.429
so it could open Kayce up to be
painted as a rogue warrior.

388
00:20:32.064 --> 00:20:35.368
Few years back.
the militia kidnapped his son.

389
00:20:35.468 --> 00:20:37.470
Word on the rez was

390
00:20:37.570 --> 00:20:39.572
Kayce took a bunch
of ranch hands.

391
00:20:39.672 --> 00:20:41.040
led an assault to get him back.

392
00:20:41.107 --> 00:20:44.110
He took on a militia
with his cowboy buddies?

393
00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:46.679
Was it extrajudicial?

394
00:20:46.779 --> 00:20:48.848
His dad was
the livestock commissioner.

395
00:20:48.948 --> 00:20:51.451
Kayce was his deputy.

396
00:20:51.584 --> 00:20:53.920
Maybe they did it
through their office.

397
00:20:54.020 --> 00:20:56.088
That's called frontier justice.

398
00:20:56.222 --> 00:20:59.091
So Clegg may have a point.

399
00:21:09.035 --> 00:21:10.770
Cal. over here.

400
00:21:29.722 --> 00:21:31.658
Please help her.

401
00:21:34.927 --> 00:21:37.897
Weak pulse.
She's barely breathing.

402
00:21:37.997 --> 00:21:39.399
Hey. are you Tom Weaver?

403
00:21:39.499 --> 00:21:41.100
Yeah.

404
00:21:41.167 --> 00:21:42.969
Well. we are U.S. Marshals. and
we're here to help you. okay?

405
00:21:43.102 --> 00:21:44.504
You got a sitrep?

406
00:21:44.604 --> 00:21:46.839
We get her off this thing.
her guts stay with it.

407
00:21:48.007 --> 00:21:49.909
All right. let's find a spot
to cut it from the tree.

408
00:21:49.976 --> 00:21:51.478
We'll just move it with her.

409
00:21:51.578 --> 00:21:54.013
Service Base.
we have the downed helo.

410
00:21:54.146 --> 00:21:55.915
and we got two survivors
in section D4.

411
00:21:55.982 --> 00:21:57.984
We're gonna need
an immediate CASEVAC.

412
00:21:58.084 --> 00:21:59.752
Repeat. an immediate CASEVAC.

413
00:21:59.852 --> 00:22:02.221
Negative.
All flights are grounded.

414
00:22:02.321 --> 00:22:03.823
Weather conditions
are worsening.

415
00:22:03.956 --> 00:22:06.426
Anything we have to cut her off
is with the horses.

416
00:22:06.493 --> 00:22:07.927
I'll be back in ten mikes.

417
00:22:07.994 --> 00:22:10.497
I'm sensing
you boys were military?

418
00:22:10.597 --> 00:22:11.831
Navy.

419
00:22:11.964 --> 00:22:16.703
My pilot. Helen.
she's a vet. too.

420
00:22:17.470 --> 00:22:19.939
Go. I'm-a stabilize Helen. okay?

421
00:22:33.319 --> 00:22:34.687
Easy.

422
00:22:39.058 --> 00:22:41.260
I didn't survive the war on
terror to be killed by a bear.

423
00:22:41.360 --> 00:22:42.962
Shotgun we left on the horse
would've helped.

424
00:22:45.031 --> 00:22:46.899
Pistols are just gonna
piss it off.

425
00:22:55.374 --> 00:22:57.243
Well. this is no good
for the pilot.

426
00:23:12.224 --> 00:23:14.260
Bear bugged out. for now.

427
00:23:14.393 --> 00:23:16.529
It didn't help. though. that
it was shaking the damn thing.

428
00:23:16.596 --> 00:23:18.831
Helen's dead.

429
00:23:23.002 --> 00:23:25.972
Why'd you make her fly
in these conditions?

430
00:23:26.072 --> 00:23:28.741
Extreme winds weren't
on any weather report.

431
00:23:28.841 --> 00:23:32.645
I'm on the clock purchasing land
over in Springhill.

432
00:23:32.745 --> 00:23:35.047
I needed to assess
the rock cover.

433
00:23:35.114 --> 00:23:38.284
Yeah? Did you get a good look
at it from the back seat?

434
00:23:38.384 --> 00:23:40.853
Helen thought
if we rebalanced the weight.

435
00:23:40.953 --> 00:23:42.855
it would help
the chopper get under control

436
00:23:42.955 --> 00:23:45.257
- when the winds kicked up.
- Well. she saved your life.

437
00:23:45.357 --> 00:23:47.460
even though you valued
your ranch more than hers.

438
00:23:47.560 --> 00:23:49.295
Hey. look.
we got to cut him loose.

439
00:23:49.428 --> 00:23:51.297
Okay?

440
00:23:51.397 --> 00:23:52.732
Yeah.

441
00:23:52.832 --> 00:23:54.834
Rotary saw or a Broco torch
here would be nice.

442
00:23:54.967 --> 00:23:56.869
If we knock out this seat.
we can probably pull him free.

443
00:23:56.969 --> 00:23:58.871
but we might break his leg
in the process.

444
00:23:58.971 --> 00:24:00.907
Go ahead.
I'm sensing you'll enjoy it.

445
00:24:00.973 --> 00:24:02.842
Yeah. well. the extraction strap

446
00:24:02.975 --> 00:24:04.410
is not gonna work
with a broken femur.

447
00:24:04.477 --> 00:24:06.513
And I can't bust you up any more

448
00:24:06.613 --> 00:24:08.515
without a plan
down this mountain.

449
00:24:08.648 --> 00:24:10.717
You have
to take Helen down. too.

450
00:24:10.817 --> 00:24:12.118
Rescue mission takes priority.

451
00:24:12.184 --> 00:24:14.186
Recovery team will get her
later. okay?

452
00:24:14.286 --> 00:24:16.789
Can you grab her wedding ring?

453
00:24:16.856 --> 00:24:21.260
Prefer her husband gets it
from me than a stranger.

454
00:24:23.763 --> 00:24:26.666
Hey. suggestion box
is open. Coyo.

455
00:24:27.600 --> 00:24:29.936
Well. since we're already
taking the seat out.

456
00:24:30.002 --> 00:24:32.404
we can use that to stabilize
his leg while we belay down.

457
00:24:32.505 --> 00:24:34.674
One of us tandems.
the other one uses the horse

458
00:24:34.774 --> 00:24:36.042
to handle the extra weight.

459
00:24:36.142 --> 00:24:37.810
Horse-assisted tandem belay.

460
00:24:37.910 --> 00:24:39.345
Okay. Missed that day in BUD/S.

461
00:24:39.445 --> 00:24:43.550
Wait. A cowboy. a SEAL
and a U.S. Marshal?

462
00:24:43.683 --> 00:24:45.151
He's also a member
of the first family

463
00:24:45.251 --> 00:24:46.553
of Montana ranchers.

464
00:24:46.686 --> 00:24:48.988
Wait. You're a Dutton?

465
00:24:49.055 --> 00:24:50.356
Yeah. Bite down on this.

466
00:24:50.456 --> 00:24:52.024
Ready?

467
00:24:52.124 --> 00:24:54.126
One. two. three.

468
00:25:02.301 --> 00:25:04.136
So. what has my crack team
learned?

469
00:25:04.203 --> 00:25:07.874
Well. it's a "he said. he said"
about whether or not

470
00:25:07.974 --> 00:25:10.543
Carson Clegg was armed
when Kayce shot him.

471
00:25:10.643 --> 00:25:12.344
That's precisely why
I tasked you

472
00:25:12.444 --> 00:25:14.080
with finding Kayce's skeletons.

473
00:25:14.180 --> 00:25:17.183
Deputy Cruz.
what's in his closet?

474
00:25:17.249 --> 00:25:21.721
Circumstances surrounding his
son's kidnapping recovery are...

475
00:25:21.821 --> 00:25:23.322
sketchy.

476
00:25:23.422 --> 00:25:25.992
Sketchy?

477
00:25:26.092 --> 00:25:27.359
How?

478
00:25:28.494 --> 00:25:33.199
It may be a case
of frontier justice.

479
00:25:33.299 --> 00:25:36.235
John Dutton
was livestock commissioner.

480
00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:38.270
and he resigned
a few weeks after.

481
00:25:38.404 --> 00:25:40.272
Giving up power is close
as a confession

482
00:25:40.406 --> 00:25:41.774
as a Dutton's capable of.

483
00:25:41.874 --> 00:25:43.275
I mean. could this be
more frontier justice?

484
00:25:43.409 --> 00:25:46.245
Did Kayce have a reason
to kill Clegg?

485
00:25:46.345 --> 00:25:48.180
Other than defending
his own life?

486
00:25:48.280 --> 00:25:49.949
Well. maybe he thought
Carson had something to do

487
00:25:50.049 --> 00:25:51.550
with his father's death
or his brother's disappearance.

488
00:25:51.618 --> 00:25:52.985
Randall Clegg was a pain
in the ass for John Dutton

489
00:25:53.085 --> 00:25:55.521
when he was
livestock commissioner.

490
00:25:55.622 --> 00:25:57.556
but that's a weak motive.

491
00:25:57.657 --> 00:25:59.425
He left a trail of bodies

492
00:25:59.558 --> 00:26:00.993
after his buddy
Chairman Rainwater

493
00:26:01.093 --> 00:26:03.062
was almost killed. didn't he?

494
00:26:03.129 --> 00:26:04.797
All justified.

495
00:26:10.369 --> 00:26:13.305
Did... Kayce have a connection

496
00:26:13.439 --> 00:26:15.107
to the Broken Rock man
the Cleggs shot?

497
00:26:15.207 --> 00:26:17.443
- Ernie Cano?
- Yeah.

498
00:26:17.543 --> 00:26:20.112
I'm not a human LinkedIn
for the rez. you know.

499
00:26:22.949 --> 00:26:25.451
Let's you and I take a drive.

500
00:26:29.756 --> 00:26:32.659
- I'll solo down. prep the horse.
- Yeah.

501
00:26:32.792 --> 00:26:34.326
Altitude's getting to me. man.

502
00:26:34.426 --> 00:26:35.995
I think it's gonna be safer
if you tandem with Weaver.

503
00:26:36.095 --> 00:26:37.496
The only guy who never puked

504
00:26:37.630 --> 00:26:39.098
in the Hindu Kush
can't handle Montana?

505
00:26:39.165 --> 00:26:41.768
I'm gonna find some branches.
stabilize his leg.

506
00:26:41.834 --> 00:26:44.804
You just tend to his wounds.
all right?

507
00:26:50.877 --> 00:26:52.645
Sorry about your father.

508
00:26:54.313 --> 00:26:57.183
I got to Montana too late
to meet him.

509
00:26:57.316 --> 00:26:59.886
but from the stories.
it seems like

510
00:26:59.986 --> 00:27:02.722
he could've taught me
a thing or two about ranching.

511
00:27:03.555 --> 00:27:05.958
Wasn't much for teaching.

512
00:27:06.025 --> 00:27:07.994
You had to learn the hard way
with him.

513
00:27:08.094 --> 00:27:10.963
Yeah. My old man
was a hard-ass. too.

514
00:27:11.063 --> 00:27:12.699
only on Wall Street.

515
00:27:15.001 --> 00:27:16.268
Working for him made me rich.

516
00:27:16.335 --> 00:27:19.438
but I was never too fond
of his shadow.

517
00:27:22.008 --> 00:27:24.610
Part of coming out here
was to escape it.

518
00:27:24.677 --> 00:27:26.278
Good luck.

519
00:27:26.378 --> 00:27:29.782
Trying to escape my dad's shadow
just led me into more darkness.

520
00:27:29.882 --> 00:27:31.818
Yeah. we don't get
to pick our fathers.

521
00:27:31.884 --> 00:27:36.222
No. but you wanting to tell
her husband yourself reminded me

522
00:27:36.322 --> 00:27:37.724
of a good thing mine once did.

523
00:27:37.824 --> 00:27:39.225
Well. I don't think

524
00:27:39.358 --> 00:27:41.493
I'll remind you of him
as a rancher.

525
00:27:41.593 --> 00:27:43.730
It's a hard living.

526
00:27:43.830 --> 00:27:46.866
You got to be all in
to have a hope of success.

527
00:27:46.966 --> 00:27:50.903
I cut my teeth
on my grandparents' ranch

528
00:27:51.003 --> 00:27:53.740
in Wyoming as a kid.

529
00:27:53.873 --> 00:27:56.408
Thought I'd...

530
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:58.377
try and build something
of my own.

531
00:27:58.477 --> 00:28:01.313
leave my family something
more than a stock portfolio.

532
00:28:03.515 --> 00:28:05.484
Hearing a crackerjack like you

533
00:28:05.551 --> 00:28:07.720
quit the cattle game
giving me pause. though.

534
00:28:07.854 --> 00:28:10.622
I'm not all out.
Still got 300 pairs.

535
00:28:10.723 --> 00:28:13.259
How do you have time for that?

536
00:28:13.359 --> 00:28:15.561
Hey. Storm's getting close.

537
00:28:15.661 --> 00:28:18.364
so let's build this and boogie.

538
00:28:20.733 --> 00:28:22.001
These are my neighbors.

539
00:28:22.068 --> 00:28:24.904
I have to be able
to face them when I go home.

540
00:28:27.573 --> 00:28:30.242
Is this Ernie Cano's room?

541
00:28:30.342 --> 00:28:31.811
Miles. wh-what's going on?

542
00:28:31.911 --> 00:28:33.913
Excuse me. Auntie.

543
00:28:34.046 --> 00:28:36.382
Marshal Gifford here would like
to speak with Ernie.

544
00:28:36.448 --> 00:28:39.418
Ernie's down in PT for his leg.

545
00:28:39.518 --> 00:28:42.088
Sorry to disturb you. We tried.

546
00:28:42.188 --> 00:28:43.689
In my experience.

547
00:28:43.790 --> 00:28:45.958
a wife knows more about her
husband's business than he does.

548
00:28:46.058 --> 00:28:48.594
Any idea
if Ernie has a relationship

549
00:28:48.694 --> 00:28:50.496
with Kayce Dutton?

550
00:28:50.596 --> 00:28:52.431
Everyone knows the white man

551
00:28:52.564 --> 00:28:54.967
who used to break horses
on the rez.

552
00:28:55.101 --> 00:28:57.603
That all? Nothing more personal?

553
00:28:57.703 --> 00:29:00.773
I never met him. but his wife
taught at Ernie's school.

554
00:29:00.873 --> 00:29:03.642
- Mm-hmm?
- He was quite fond of her.

555
00:29:03.776 --> 00:29:05.812
We both were.

556
00:29:06.645 --> 00:29:08.347
You don't say. ma'am.

557
00:29:09.215 --> 00:29:11.417
Do tell more.

558
00:29:14.954 --> 00:29:17.723
Lightning strikes
are getting close.

559
00:29:29.701 --> 00:29:31.871
Okay. come on.

560
00:29:32.972 --> 00:29:35.274
Come on. Back. back.

561
00:29:36.142 --> 00:29:37.709
Come on.

562
00:29:38.477 --> 00:29:40.012
Steady.

563
00:29:40.146 --> 00:29:41.881
How you doing?

564
00:29:41.981 --> 00:29:44.083
Don't focus on me.

565
00:29:46.285 --> 00:29:47.686
Come on.

566
00:30:01.433 --> 00:30:02.801
Come on.

567
00:30:22.154 --> 00:30:23.689
You good?

568
00:30:23.789 --> 00:30:25.157
- Throw us a line.
- Yeah!

569
00:30:27.059 --> 00:30:29.228
Our collar just used
our shotgun against us

570
00:30:29.328 --> 00:30:30.696
and beat feet into the woods.

571
00:30:30.829 --> 00:30:31.864
I'm-a pursue.

572
00:30:31.998 --> 00:30:34.000
And leave two men behind
this time?

573
00:30:44.010 --> 00:30:45.577
Come on.

574
00:30:51.884 --> 00:30:54.120
Sorry. sorry.

575
00:30:58.524 --> 00:30:59.658
All right.
you get him down the hill.

576
00:30:59.725 --> 00:31:01.493
I'm-a pursue that recluse.

577
00:31:01.593 --> 00:31:04.230
One is none. right?
Mission's not over.

578
00:31:04.330 --> 00:31:05.731
Please.

579
00:31:05.831 --> 00:31:07.900
I'm responsible for
a high enough body count today.

580
00:31:10.937 --> 00:31:12.438
All right. man.
let's get off this mountain

581
00:31:12.538 --> 00:31:14.473
before it throws
anything else at us.

582
00:31:14.573 --> 00:31:16.742
Come on. One. two. three.

583
00:31:20.779 --> 00:31:22.614
How was your field trip?

584
00:31:22.748 --> 00:31:24.150
It was enlightening.

585
00:31:24.250 --> 00:31:25.884
We learned that Dutton
killed the man

586
00:31:25.985 --> 00:31:28.887
who had tried to kill someone
important to his late wife.

587
00:31:28.988 --> 00:31:31.790
Meaning what. exactly?

588
00:31:31.890 --> 00:31:33.926
Well. Ernie and Monica Dutton
worked together.

589
00:31:34.026 --> 00:31:36.228
They grew so close that
he and his wife used to have

590
00:31:36.295 --> 00:31:39.731
Monica and her son over for
dinner when Kayce was deployed.

591
00:31:39.798 --> 00:31:41.100
We don't know if Kayce

592
00:31:41.233 --> 00:31:42.801
knew any of their history.

593
00:31:42.901 --> 00:31:44.903
Clegg just needs
to whisper that to the press.

594
00:31:44.971 --> 00:31:47.273
and they will have a field day
exploiting the Dutton name.

595
00:31:47.373 --> 00:31:50.376
Think anyone in this unit
will have a career after that?

596
00:31:50.476 --> 00:31:52.911
Now. I'm informing the Office
of Professional Responsibility

597
00:31:52.979 --> 00:31:55.147
- of the connection.
- You're feeding Kayce

598
00:31:55.247 --> 00:31:57.083
to the wolves
based off a theory.

599
00:31:57.149 --> 00:32:00.987
I'm keeping this team away
from his blast radius.

600
00:32:01.087 --> 00:32:04.456
You can file that under
"if you want a job done right."

601
00:32:10.729 --> 00:32:14.333
You can't pull a badge
over dots that may not connect.

602
00:32:15.167 --> 00:32:17.736
Government's the windshield.
rest of us are bugs.

603
00:32:20.306 --> 00:32:23.675
Okay. You were on
Kayce's six during the incident.

604
00:32:23.809 --> 00:32:27.679
So. walk us through it again.
from the start.

605
00:32:30.449 --> 00:32:32.884
We all pursued the Cleggs
to their hunting grounds.

606
00:32:32.985 --> 00:32:35.587
Kayce and I broke off
from the team to outflank them.

607
00:32:35.687 --> 00:32:36.855
pushed up the hill.

608
00:32:36.955 --> 00:32:39.791
Took fire from two positions?

609
00:32:40.592 --> 00:32:42.761
First.
we got separated by the I.E.D.

610
00:32:44.163 --> 00:32:45.664
Wait. A decorated Navy SEAL

611
00:32:45.764 --> 00:32:48.534
missed a trip wire?

612
00:32:49.335 --> 00:32:50.836
There's no chance.

613
00:32:50.936 --> 00:32:53.105
Maybe it was detonated

614
00:32:53.172 --> 00:32:54.540
remotely?

615
00:32:56.275 --> 00:32:57.943
Wes and Carson
were behind cover.

616
00:32:58.010 --> 00:32:59.945
They didn't have eyes on us yet.

617
00:33:06.485 --> 00:33:07.853
Avoided my worst nightmare

618
00:33:07.986 --> 00:33:09.355
thanks to you two.

619
00:33:09.455 --> 00:33:11.923
Lost track of how many times
you saved me today.

620
00:33:13.659 --> 00:33:15.827
Wish we could've
saved everyone. sir.

621
00:33:18.030 --> 00:33:19.531
Yeah.

622
00:33:30.008 --> 00:33:33.745
That's some U-turn you just
pulled on that transplant.

623
00:33:34.846 --> 00:33:37.149
Yeah. I might've
pegged him wrong.

624
00:33:37.249 --> 00:33:38.950
Yeah. Let's get back. man.
'cause I want to dig into

625
00:33:39.051 --> 00:33:40.452
that guy who almost
mudsucked us.

626
00:33:40.552 --> 00:33:42.988
Rather face off with that bear
than see Gifford.

627
00:33:43.055 --> 00:33:46.192
Yeah. I get it. but...
I ain't got no worries.

628
00:33:46.292 --> 00:33:47.926
You gonna be good on that front.

629
00:33:48.060 --> 00:33:50.862
It's the law of nature. right?

630
00:34:05.377 --> 00:34:06.912
Look. I'm sorry. Cal.

631
00:34:07.012 --> 00:34:09.547
Looks like Dutton's goose
is cooked.

632
00:34:09.614 --> 00:34:11.250
Oh. so you can prove that Clegg

633
00:34:11.350 --> 00:34:13.619
- was unarmed then. huh?
- Well. not exactly.

634
00:34:13.752 --> 00:34:15.521
But this office needs to project
a proactive stance

635
00:34:15.587 --> 00:34:16.987
against abuse of the badge.

636
00:34:17.089 --> 00:34:19.690
OPR has cleared the way
for you to fire Dutton

637
00:34:19.757 --> 00:34:21.327
before they finish their review.

638
00:34:21.427 --> 00:34:23.529
I warned you
hiring him was a mistake.

639
00:34:23.629 --> 00:34:25.097
Now you can correct that.

640
00:34:25.197 --> 00:34:28.967
You know. the last time
I ended a teammate's career.

641
00:34:29.067 --> 00:34:31.437
cost them everything. so...

642
00:34:31.536 --> 00:34:36.175
you want his badge so bad.
do it yourself.

643
00:34:37.208 --> 00:34:38.643
Check this out.

644
00:34:39.745 --> 00:34:42.214
We had the sheriff
search the scene again.

645
00:34:42.313 --> 00:34:43.715
looking for ways
the Cleggs might've had eyes

646
00:34:43.782 --> 00:34:46.618
on Kayce and Miles
while engaged in a gunfight.

647
00:34:46.717 --> 00:34:49.655
They found trail cams
from a grad student in Missoula

648
00:34:49.755 --> 00:34:52.623
studying gray-crowned
rosy finches.

649
00:34:52.724 --> 00:34:55.827
Did the sheriff miss the trail
cams in the initial processing?

650
00:34:55.927 --> 00:34:58.664
They're under-resourced
and looking for a missing gun.

651
00:34:58.764 --> 00:35:01.099
There was a node
on one of the cams.

652
00:35:01.200 --> 00:35:03.169
The Cleggs were piggybacking
off of it for hunting.

653
00:35:09.074 --> 00:35:11.042
That's Carson Clegg.

654
00:35:14.513 --> 00:35:17.316
Weapon firmly in hand.

655
00:35:24.956 --> 00:35:27.593
- How's that for thorough?
- "Abuse of the badge"

656
00:35:27.693 --> 00:35:31.997
looks pretty damn heroic
to me. Harry. Hmm?

657
00:35:32.831 --> 00:35:34.166
Glad you cleared this up.

658
00:35:34.266 --> 00:35:36.702
I'll tell OPR to shove it.

659
00:35:37.636 --> 00:35:39.405
Good work.

660
00:35:45.377 --> 00:35:46.878
Hey.

661
00:35:47.813 --> 00:35:51.082
It's true I'd rather be back
in D.C. than here.

662
00:35:51.183 --> 00:35:54.653
But not so much
that it turns me into a rat.

663
00:35:55.954 --> 00:35:58.624
Don't ever play me
like that again.

664
00:36:15.140 --> 00:36:18.810
Everybody. meet the man
who saved my life.

665
00:36:18.910 --> 00:36:20.045
Kayce Dutton.

666
00:36:24.049 --> 00:36:26.418
Figured a rancher needs his hat.

667
00:36:26.518 --> 00:36:30.389
Oh. this thing is filthy
and this room is sterile.

668
00:36:31.557 --> 00:36:34.693
That. uh. land out in Springhill
you were assaying?

669
00:36:35.827 --> 00:36:37.396
Belongs to the Quinns?

670
00:36:37.529 --> 00:36:39.030
It does.

671
00:36:39.831 --> 00:36:42.768
They went bust
overgrazing their pastures.

672
00:36:42.868 --> 00:36:44.169
It's gonna take
at least two seasons

673
00:36:44.236 --> 00:36:46.472
before it's fit
for cattle again.

674
00:36:48.574 --> 00:36:53.245
You saved my life
and my pocketbook today.

675
00:36:53.379 --> 00:36:55.247
I'm in your debt.

676
00:36:55.381 --> 00:36:57.883
Yeah. We all are.

677
00:36:58.784 --> 00:37:01.620
- Enjoy your family. sir.
- Now. hold-hold on.

678
00:37:03.455 --> 00:37:06.124
I need you out there
protecting Montanans

679
00:37:06.258 --> 00:37:09.160
without having to worry
about your ranch.

680
00:37:09.961 --> 00:37:11.463
Let me lend you some hands.

681
00:37:11.597 --> 00:37:13.465
Aw. I can't accept that.

682
00:37:13.599 --> 00:37:16.902
Hmm. When my father
makes you an offer.

683
00:37:16.968 --> 00:37:18.970
you don't have a choice.

684
00:37:19.104 --> 00:37:22.040
You had my back today. Kayce.

685
00:37:22.107 --> 00:37:24.843
It's only right I say thank you.

686
00:37:29.881 --> 00:37:31.783
You let Kayce know
he's in the clear. right?

687
00:37:31.883 --> 00:37:35.587
Mm-hmm. I left him a message.
but haven't heard back.

688
00:37:36.722 --> 00:37:38.424
I'm sure he doesn't think
our pack protected him today.

689
00:37:38.490 --> 00:37:41.393
Well. I get a sense
that he's used to others

690
00:37:41.460 --> 00:37:43.695
failing to stand up for him.

691
00:37:43.795 --> 00:37:45.631
Yeah. after digging
into his past.

692
00:37:45.731 --> 00:37:47.933
seems trouble's been
hunting Kayce his whole life.

693
00:37:47.999 --> 00:37:49.768
Yet he's still standing.

694
00:37:49.868 --> 00:37:53.238
Yeah. but it comes
at a hell of a price.

695
00:37:53.339 --> 00:37:54.706
- Look who it is.
- Oh.

696
00:37:54.806 --> 00:37:56.642
You beg me to come out
just so I can watch y'all

697
00:37:56.775 --> 00:37:58.677
cry in your beers?

698
00:37:59.445 --> 00:38:01.079
You saved my ass
with the Cleggs.

699
00:38:01.179 --> 00:38:02.514
I had no idea.

700
00:38:02.614 --> 00:38:04.916
Well. I had your back
just like you had mine.

701
00:38:05.016 --> 00:38:06.284
Well. the upside is.

702
00:38:06.385 --> 00:38:07.853
pretty sure we got Gifford
off your ass.

703
00:38:07.986 --> 00:38:10.021
Doubt that's the last time
I'll deal with him.

704
00:38:10.121 --> 00:38:11.823
- Or the Cleggs.
- Hey. check this out.

705
00:38:11.957 --> 00:38:14.360
I think we let
one of America's Most Wanted go.

706
00:38:14.460 --> 00:38:16.762
Specifically. Rudy Carpenter.

707
00:38:16.828 --> 00:38:19.465
Come on. Does that not
look like the eyes of the guy

708
00:38:19.531 --> 00:38:20.899
- who shot at us?
- "Serial bomber

709
00:38:20.999 --> 00:38:22.634
on the lam for three years"
Rudy Carpenter?

710
00:38:22.734 --> 00:38:24.836
Yeah. it would explain
why he was gunning for us.

711
00:38:24.936 --> 00:38:27.305
We can't
just ignore this. right?

712
00:38:30.241 --> 00:38:31.577
Oh. uh...

713
00:38:31.677 --> 00:38:33.244
Everybody. this is Dolly Weaver.

714
00:38:33.345 --> 00:38:35.180
Hi. I don't mean
to crash the party.

715
00:38:35.280 --> 00:38:37.349
but my father insisted

716
00:38:37.449 --> 00:38:39.184
on buying drinks
for the people who saved the job

717
00:38:39.284 --> 00:38:40.986
- of the man who saved his life.
- I'll drink to that.

718
00:38:41.086 --> 00:38:42.588
Hell yeah.

719
00:38:42.688 --> 00:38:44.756
Yes. thank you.

720
00:38:46.825 --> 00:38:48.694
Kayce.

721
00:38:48.794 --> 00:38:50.328
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

722
00:38:50.396 --> 00:38:51.363
Thanks to you.

723
00:38:51.497 --> 00:38:52.531
- Cheers.
- Yeah. All right.

724
00:38:52.664 --> 00:38:53.832
To your father.

725
00:38:53.899 --> 00:38:56.668
Thank you. Seriously.

726
00:38:59.204 --> 00:39:00.806
You know. for what it's worth.

727
00:39:00.906 --> 00:39:02.708
I hated turning your world
upside down.

728
00:39:02.808 --> 00:39:05.744
Nothing my dad despised more
than internal affairs.

729
00:39:05.844 --> 00:39:07.979
- We're all good.
- Oh. good day for you.

730
00:39:08.046 --> 00:39:10.248
You kept your badge
and you made a new friend.

731
00:39:10.348 --> 00:39:13.385
She's just grateful
we saved her dad.

732
00:39:13.519 --> 00:39:15.421
Oh. I know what grateful
looks like.

733
00:39:15.554 --> 00:39:17.456
and that is not
how she's eyeing you.

734
00:39:17.556 --> 00:39:19.491
Saddle up. cowboy.

735
00:39:23.395 --> 00:39:25.531
Okay. look. I have questions

736
00:39:25.597 --> 00:39:27.499
about how you two
arrived here together.

737
00:39:27.566 --> 00:39:31.737
but I'm just happy. man.
that you're here at all.

738
00:39:31.837 --> 00:39:34.406
Well. the fact that we can keep
that family's world

739
00:39:34.506 --> 00:39:38.744
from falling apart...
justified and right.

740
00:39:38.877 --> 00:39:40.211
Yeah.

741
00:39:40.278 --> 00:39:43.214
Well. maybe the badge
is a... a path to penance.

742
00:40:00.265 --> 00:40:02.901
Upset Dolly robbed you
of a chance to buy another round

743
00:40:03.001 --> 00:40:04.536
from your favorite bartender?

744
00:40:06.237 --> 00:40:08.039
Yeah.

745
00:40:08.139 --> 00:40:12.277
She seemed so scared not knowing
if her dad was dead or alive.

746
00:40:12.377 --> 00:40:13.745
Well. she's lucky to have

747
00:40:13.812 --> 00:40:15.413
that kind of relationship
with him.

748
00:40:18.950 --> 00:40:20.385
He's lucky. Yeah.

749
00:40:23.722 --> 00:40:25.491
Hmm.

750
00:40:25.624 --> 00:40:27.025
Bartender's my kid.

751
00:40:32.464 --> 00:40:34.232
Maddie.

752
00:40:34.332 --> 00:40:37.268
Been out of her life. uh.

753
00:40:37.335 --> 00:40:39.170
over 20 years.

754
00:40:39.270 --> 00:40:41.740
She's your daughter?

755
00:40:42.508 --> 00:40:45.544
I took this posting
to move closer to her. but...

756
00:40:46.978 --> 00:40:48.947
It's becoming clear that.
you know.

757
00:40:49.047 --> 00:40:53.018
she'd rather have me
out of her life than in her bar.

758
00:40:54.820 --> 00:40:56.955
Cal.

759
00:40:59.324 --> 00:41:00.692
Give it time.

760
00:41:06.498 --> 00:41:07.533
Time.

761
00:41:10.468 --> 00:41:11.870
Right.

762
00:41:31.857 --> 00:41:34.159
All the skills
my dad says you have.

763
00:41:34.259 --> 00:41:36.361
it seems like life of
the party's not one of them.

764
00:41:37.929 --> 00:41:39.297
I'm definitely more comfortable
driving cattle

765
00:41:39.364 --> 00:41:40.832
than being jammed in like one.

766
00:41:40.899 --> 00:41:43.134
Hmm.

767
00:41:43.234 --> 00:41:45.804
Well. your teammates seem nice.

768
00:41:45.871 --> 00:41:49.975
Glad you all are out here
keeping people safe.

769
00:41:50.075 --> 00:41:51.910
Makes Montana less scary.

770
00:41:52.010 --> 00:41:54.212
Montana's not scary.

771
00:41:54.980 --> 00:41:56.982
Just have to get to know it.

772
00:41:57.082 --> 00:41:59.017
Hmm.

773
00:41:59.117 --> 00:42:01.587
Oh. well. wish I knew a local

774
00:42:01.687 --> 00:42:04.522
that could give me a crash
course in all things Big Sky.

775
00:42:07.225 --> 00:42:10.295
Wait. you were
born and raised here.

776
00:42:11.296 --> 00:42:12.363
What do you say?

777
00:42:15.701 --> 00:42:17.068
Maybe.
